Theorem 1 shows the existence and uniqueness of the NE b˚ for the new game, and Corollary 1 gives three conditions that are satisﬁed by b˚. Through these theorems, it is possible to solve the original game by ﬁnding the relation between b˚ and n˚. Now let’s look at the relation in the next theorem.

