Since these two equations are negative, F ps, Bq is a concave function. Therefore, there is a unique maximum point, and the equation has an optimal solution.
In addition, we can ﬁnd the unique maximum point ps˚, B˚q and the unique maximum value F ps˚, B˚q by using the gradient descent method. In this process, we used the MATLAB program to ﬁnd the optimal solution for the parameters in Table 3, as follows:

F ps˚, B˚q “ 186.93 at ps˚, B˚q “ p1.35, 23.79q. (22)

