C. EXPERIMENT : POSTURE ASSESSMENT DATA In the previous steps, we have checked that the proposed model is well deﬁned, the optimization problem is truly globally optimized, and the NE points actually maximize the utility of the data source. In this step, we use a real-world data [8], [38], [39] to implement the proposed model. The data used in these papers are the trunk and shoulder postures of workers collected for 80 working days in three differ-
